AppiumIntro&DownloadInstall2

------------------------------------
Prerequisite to use APPIUM (Windows)
-------------------------------------
Pre-requisites:-----
Install Java (JDK)
Eclipse
Maven plugin for Eclipse
TestNG plugin for Eclipse
Selenium Standalone Server

Android Tools:-----
Android Studio
Appium Server/Appium Desktop
Appium Client Library1 Â  

*SET JAVA FIRST
1. Download JDK JAVA - .exe File 
2. Install & Check-In Program Files (Copy The Location)
3. Go To Advanced System Setting 'This PC'
4. Select Environment Variable -> System Variable -> Set Path 'JAVA_HOME'
5. Download Android STUDIO -> Official Page 
6. Install & Copy The SDK Path (C:\Users\Karan\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk)

*OPEN ANDROID STUDIO & CONFIGURE EMULATOR
1. Install & start the Appium server via Node.js 
-Download Node - Official website for Windows 
-Install & Finish 
-It will automatically install some other Tools For Node using Powershell 

*SET (ANDROID SDK & NODE) HOME PATH IN WINDOWS SYSTEM VARIABLES
-Check where is SDK Installed
-Copy the Path (C:\Users\Karan\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk)
-Open Environments Variables -> System Variables -> Paste AS 'ANDROID_HOME'

**Start Android Studio  (C:\Program Files\Android\Android Studio\bin -> click to Studio64)
**Click To new project tab To Move to Home page -> To make some setting 
**Wait untill build got finished
**Now Go To 'Tools'
**Select SDK MANAGER -> SDK TOOLS 
**Uncheck 'Hide absolute packages'
**Now you will see in list 'Android SDK Tools(absolute)'
**Check that -> Ok & Apply 
** Accept & wait till Done 
** Now you will see tools folder (C:\Users\Karan\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk)<-- In This Location
** Now Copy this Location Under tools (C:\Users\Karan\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk\tools\bin)
*** Add this under Environment Variable -> New -> PATH -> Paste this -> C:\Users\Karan\AppData\Local\Android\Sdk\tools\bin

**Go to Program Files 
**copy node location : C:\Program Files\nodejs
**Create New variable under System Variables & Paste the location 'NODE_HOME'
**Copy NPM location : C:\Program Files\nodejs\node_modules\npm\bin
**Go to PATH -> Add this : C:\Program Files\nodejs\node_modules\npm\bin

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Start Android Studio & Install Appium Server & Configure Virtual & Real Devices/ Emulators
1. open Android sdk 
2. tools -> Device Manager
3. Create Virtual Device -> Select The Phone & Version "Created"
4. Virtual Device Runned By clicking PLAY ICON 

1. Open Terminal 
2. Run this command : npm install appium
3. AFTER THAT : npm install -g appium (Open terminal as a administrator mode) then run this 















